post_text: As a reminder for all patrons attending conference sporting events at PCM (Jr./Sr. High volleyball), The Heart of Iowa has approved a mandate requiring masks to be worn by all attendees when they enter the building and keep them on until they enter the gymnasium. Patrons are also required to wear a mask when they are in common areas (such as our concession stand line, commons, and restrooms). In addition, all children grade 8 and under must be supervised by an adult at all times. These are rules that have been put into place by the HOIAC conference and we kindly ask all PCM fans to follow them.

post_text:
Adult ($90) and Student ($35) activity passes are available for purchase for the 2020-21 school year. The family pass is no longer available. These can be purchased from the school website under Online Bill Pay > Food & Fee Payments...same location you would put money into your children's lunch accounts or pay registration fees.

Adults and staff will still receive a laminated cardstock pass as normal. Students will be issued a temporary unlaminated cardstock pass. Any passes for a parent/student will be sent to the school your student attends and sent home with them. If there are multiple students, passes will be sent home with the oldest student.

School pictures are in mid September and we'll receive the new student passes shortly after that and distribute them to replace the cardstock pass. Any questions can be directed to Kim Pettyjohn at kpettyjohn@pcmschools.org.

Parents and community members of PCM Schools,

The Campfire before/after school daycare program will not be available for the 2020-2021 school year at PCE. At this time, their plans are to try to start the service again for the 2021-22 school year, as long as PCE has ample room to offer them. This has been a great partnership and a valued service to our families, so we will do what we can to support it again in the future. Thank you.
text:
Parents and community members of PCM Schools,

The Campfire before/after school daycare program will not be available for the 2020-2021 school year at PCE. At this time, their plans are to try to start the service again for the 2021-22 school year, as long as PCE has ample room to offer them. This has been a great partnership and a valued service to our families, so we will do what we can to support it again in the future. Thank you.

We are currently accepting online registration of students for the 2020-2021 school year.

Visit www.pcmschools.org, click on "Resources" across the top, then "Registration".

**Online registration will close on Friday, August 14th at 3:00pm

**District Personnel will be at the High School in Monroe on Tuesday, July 28th from 2:00 p.m - 7:00 p.m. to assist you with your registration process.

If you have any issues registering, contact the office from the school your child will attend. All secretaries are currently on summer hours and are not in the office all five days. If needed, please leave a message and they will call you back.

PCM Parents & Students:

We are closing this survey tonight at 10pm, if you haven't completed this survey, I highly encourage everyone to participate.

We are asking all parents and students to please take time to complete the Technology & Learning Survey with the link provided below. This particular survey's data will be crucial for administration to visualize our district's strengths and areas of improvement with distance learning. The results will provide a blueprint for administrators to proactively plan for all possible ways of delivering education next fall. The survey will take 5-10 minutes. Your participation is greatly appreciated!

post_text:
PCM Students & Parents,

Starting Monday, June 1st, we will begin computer turn in for Middle School students. Please park in the south lot in front of the gym. We will have a volunteer letting students in to clean and turn in their equipment. We are asking for students to please adhere to social distancing while waiting inside the gym. PCM Parents,

Starting Tuesday, May 26th from 12pm to 7pm, High School students will begin turning in computers for the summer. Students will park in the main lot. In order to adequately plan for graduation and prom, the district will make a decision about the status of graduation and prom on the proposed make-up dates released last month several weeks in advance. The dates for a decision will be as follows:

June
Prom make-up date 1: 6/19
Graduation make-up date 1: 6/28
Decision date: 6/5

July
Prom make-up date 2: 7/10
Graduation make-up date 2: 7/12
Decision date: 6/26

If there are still mandates surrounding the number of people that can be gathered that will impact the proposed July dates, prom will unfortunately be canceled and the district will examine a virtual graduation option. The health and well-being of our students is of utmost importance to us, so these decisions will not be made lightly. Thank you.

COVID - 19 Update - April 20, 2020

post_text:
Dear PCM Mustang Families,

I am saddened to share that Iowa Governor Kim Reynolds announced that Iowa schools will now be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. I am saddened that we won't be able to bring closure to this school year as we have in past years. I know we are all missing the day-to-day interaction with each other. More updates and information will be shared early next week regarding our plans for the rest of this school year.

Announcements regarding spring activities will most likely be made later today from the various Iowa activity and athletic governing agencies. A decision regarding summer activities and athletics will be made at a later date.

Mr. Jermeland

post_text:
Dear Parents,

On Saturday, March 14th , 2020, Prairie City Police Department, Jasper County Sheriff’s Office, and the PCM School District will conduct a rescue task force mock exercise. School staff, Fire, EMS and Law Enforcement responders will practice the response utilizing Rescue Task Force Principles and the National Incident Management System. The exercise will take place at Prairie City Elementary School and the PCM Middle School site. The exercise will start at 8:00am and end at 12:00 noon.

The purpose of this exercise is to evaluate response procedures to active shooter incidents. The Information
reinforced and lessons learned from this exercise will be used to revise RTF policies and procedures as needed and
implement them countywide.

We will need fifteen to twenty student and adult volunteers for this event. Please contact Kim Pettyjohn at
kpettyjohn@pcmschools.org or call 641 259 2316 to indicate that you would like to volunteer for the event.

Sincerely,

Mr. Jermeland
Superintendent
